  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Save Hope of 6,800 Girls drop out of school Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will save 6,800 vulnerable girls from dropping out of school by providing a Package of scholastic materials, Uniforms, school fees and training on sanitary pads making as Menstrual Hygiene and management approach for girl child school retention in Eastern and Northern Uganda. The project targets 24 schools to boost education of girls affected by Poverty, war trauma, and cultural practices including early marriage. 12 boreholes will be drilled in 12 schools and nearby communities.</narrative>
  </description>
